Time Limit: 4 sec
Memory: 256 MB

Description
Given an array of N integers, Q queries, and an integer K. In each query two integers L, R is given, you have to find

(A[L] + A[L+1] * K + A[L+2] * K^2 + …. + A[R] * K^(R-L)) % 10^9+7.

Input Format
The first line contains three space-separated integers N, Q, K where 1 <= N <= 10^6, 1 <= Q <= 10^6, 1 <= K <= 10^9.

Next line contains N space-separated integers (-10^9 <= Ai <= 10^9).

Next Q lines contain two space-separated integers L, R where 1 <= L <= R <= N.

Output Format
For each query print the value of

(A[L] + A[L+1] * K + A[L+2] * K^2 + …. + A[R] * K^(R-L)) % 10^9+7

in a new line.

Constraints

Sample Input 1

```
10 10 234565
12 -23 -123 2345 2345 44 345 -93945 -5353 1
1 5
